# Shared Types

All payload and domain types shared between the frontend (`apps/web`) and backend (`apps/server`) must be defined in `packages/types/src/` and imported via `@repo/types`.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — defined once in packages/types, consumed by both apps
import type { User, CreateUserPayload } from '@repo/types';

// ❌ BAD — local type that duplicates a shared contract
interface CreateUserPayload {
  email: string;
  name?: string;
}
```

## When to add a type here

- API request/response payloads
- Shared domain interfaces (e.g. `User`, `Post`)
- Any type imported by more than one app or package

## When NOT to add it here

- UI-only types (component props, local state shapes)
- Server-only internals (entity classes, ORM models)
- Types that are never used outside a single package

## Export pattern

Add the export to `packages/types/src/index.ts`:

```typescript
export type { User, CreateUserPayload, UpdateUserPayload } from './user';
```

Then re-run `pnpm build` in the `db` or `types` package if the consuming app can't resolve it.
